---
export const prerender = true;
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base title="process" miscTitle="process" showAnnouncement={false}>
  <article class="doc">
    <header class="doc__head">
      <p class="doc__kicker">// case study &middot; graphic design</p>
      <h1 class="doc__title">the process.</h1>
      <p class="doc__lede">
        Tokyo Zero is a small-drop anime merch project &mdash; 47 products, three thematic
        storefronts, one voice. Here's how the brand system, typography, and page
        architecture came together.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="sec">
      <p class="sec__num">01</p>
      <h2 class="sec__h">voice + audience</h2>
      <p>
        The core reader is the person who already knows the reference &mdash; Panty &amp; Stocking with
        Garterbelt, Needy Streamer Overload, Genshin, HoYo, Vtubers. The brand assumes fluency
        instead of explaining. Copy is short, lowercase, punchy &mdash; closer to a Discord message
        than a marketing brochure.
      </p>
      <blockquote class="pull">
        "small drops. heavy print. character work for the people who already know."
      </blockquote>
    </section>

    <section class="sec">
      <p class="sec__num">02</p>
      <h2 class="sec__h">three storefronts, one system</h2>
      <div class="grid grid--3">
        <div class="tile">
          <p class="tile__label">misc</p>
          <h3 class="tile__title">catalog, curated</h3>
          <p>Magazine-style catalog with numbered cards, hairline dividers, slate-violet accent. The neutral hub.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tile">
          <p class="tile__label">psg</p>
          <h3 class="tile__title">candy-halftone spectacle</h3>
          <p>Panty &amp; Stocking pastiche &mdash; hot pink frills, halftone circles, 7-card showcase on a tilted cyan slab.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tile">
          <p class="tile__label">nso</p>
          <h3 class="tile__title">crt streamer decay</h3>
          <p>Needy Streamer Overload homage &mdash; chrome bg, RGB-glitching popups, scanlines everywhere.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="sec">
      <p class="sec__num">03</p>
      <h2 class="sec__h">typography</h2>
      <div class="grid grid--2">
        <div class="face">
          <p class="face__name">Apex Mk3</p>
          <p class="face__sample" style="font-family: 'Apex Mk3', monospace;">.contact</p>
          <p class="face__role">Monospace. Titles, labels, navigation. Reads as terminal output &mdash; matches the design + code story.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="face">
          <p class="face__name">Beam Visionary</p>
          <p class="face__sample" style="font-family: 'Beam Visionary', cursive; font-style: italic;">from the desk.</p>
          <p class="face__role">Script. Eyebrows, brand marks. The one moment of handwriting in an otherwise-mechanical system.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="face">
          <p class="face__name">Branding Pro</p>
          <p class="face__sample" style="font-family: 'Branding Pro', sans-serif;">Body copy &mdash; running text.</p>
          <p class="face__role">Sans. Body copy. Neutral, wide x-height, five weights. Does the invisible work.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="face">
          <p class="face__name">NSO CRT</p>
          <p class="face__sample" style="font-family: 'NSO CRT', monospace; letter-spacing: 0.06em;">SIGNAL &gt; NO SYNC</p>
          <p class="face__role">Pixel bitmap. NSO theme only. Chyrons, popup labels, HUD text.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="sec">
      <p class="sec__num">04</p>
      <h2 class="sec__h">color</h2>
      <p>
        Base palette locks the catalog in a soft-white / slate-violet universe. Each themed room
        breaks that mold on purpose. Themes feel like walking into different shops; misc is the
        hallway between.
      </p>
      <div class="swatches">
        <div class="sw"><span style="background: #f5f4f0"></span>#f5f4f0 base</div>
        <div class="sw"><span style="background: #14131a"></span>#14131a ink</div>
        <div class="sw"><span style="background: #5061b9"></span>#5061b9 slate-violet</div>
        <div class="sw"><span style="background: #ff4da6"></span>#ff4da6 psg pink</div>
        <div class="sw"><span style="background: #3deaff"></span>#3deaff psg cyan</div>
        <div class="sw"><span style="background: #fd7ac0"></span>#fd7ac0 nso magenta</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="sec sec--cta">
      <p class="sec__cta-kicker">// next</p>
      <h2 class="sec__cta-h">how it ships &rarr;</h2>
      <p>
        The whole storefront runs on a serverless AWS stack.
        <a href="/architecture/">Walk through the infrastructure</a> or
        <a href="/catalog/">browse the catalog</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>

  <style>
    .doc { max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; padding: clamp(48px, 8vw, 96px) clamp(24px, 6vw, 48px); }
    .doc__head { margin-bottom: 8vh; }
    .doc__kicker {
      font-family: 'Apex Mk3', 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--misc-accent, #5061b9);
      margin: 0 0 20px;
    }
    .doc__title {
      font-family: 'Apex Mk3', sans-serif;
      font-weight: 300;
      font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, 3.6rem);
      line-height: 1;
      margin: 0 0 24px;
      text-transform: lowercase;
    }
    .doc__lede {
      font-family: 'Branding Pro', sans-serif;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      line-height: 1.55;
      color: var(--misc-ink-soft, #6b6b6b);
      margin: 0;
      max-width: 620px;
    }
    .sec { margin-bottom: 8vh; }
    .sec__num {
      font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
      font-size: 0.7rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      color: var(--misc-accent, #5061b9);
      margin: 0 0 6px;
    }
    .sec__h {
      font-family: 'Apex Mk3', sans-serif;
      font-weight: 400;
      font-size: 1.4rem;
      color: var(--misc-ink, #1a1a1a);
      margin: 0 0 20px;
      padding-bottom: 12px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--misc-line, rgba(0,0,0,0.14));
      text-transform: lowercase;
    }
    .sec p, .sec li { font-family: 'Branding Pro', sans-serif; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0 0 16px; color: var(--misc-ink); }
    .pull {
      margin: 24px 0 0;
      padding: 20px 24px;
      background: rgba(80, 97, 185, 0.08);
      border-left: 3px solid var(--misc-accent, #5061b9);
      font-family: 'Beam Visionary', cursive;
      font-style: italic;
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      line-height: 1.4;
      color: var(--misc-ink, #1a1a1a);
    }
    .grid { display: grid; gap: 20px; margin-top: 20px; }
    .grid--2 { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .grid--3 { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr; }
    .tile, .face {
      padding: 20px;
      background: #fff;
      border: 1px solid var(--misc-line, rgba(0,0,0,0.14));
      clip-path: polygon(0 0, calc(100% - 10px) 0, 100% 10px, 100% 100%, 0 100%);
    }
    .tile__label, .face__name {
      font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
      font-size: 0.68rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.18em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--misc-accent, #5061b9);
      margin: 0 0 10px;
    }
    .tile__title {
      font-family: 'Apex Mk3', sans-serif;
      font-weight: 400;
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      margin: 0 0 10px;
      color: var(--misc-ink);
    }
    .tile p, .face__role { font-size: 0.9rem; margin: 0; color: var(--misc-ink-soft); }
    .face__sample { font-size: 1.5rem; margin: 4px 0 14px; line-height: 1.1; color: var(--misc-ink); }
    .swatches { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(140px, 1fr)); gap: 12px; margin-top: 20px; }
    .sw { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--misc-ink-soft); }
    .sw span { display: inline-block; width: 26px; height: 26px; border: 1px solid var(--misc-line); }

    .sec--cta { padding: 28px; background: rgba(80, 97, 185, 0.06); border: 1px solid rgba(80,97,185,0.14); clip-path: polygon(0 0, calc(100% - 14px) 0, 100% 14px, 100% 100%, 0 100%); }
    .sec__cta-kicker {
      font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
      font-size: 0.7rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      color: var(--misc-accent);
      margin: 0 0 8px;
    }
    .sec__cta-h { font-family: 'Apex Mk3', sans-serif; font-size: 1.6rem; margin: 0 0 12px; font-weight: 300; text-transform: lowercase; }
    .sec--cta p { margin: 0; }
    .sec--cta a { color: var(--misc-accent); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; }

    @media (max-width: 700px) {
      .grid--2, .grid--3 { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }
  </style>
</Base>
